WEBVTT

00:00.890 --> 00:02.755
WE'RE AT BIG TOP BURGER?

00:02.790 --> 00:04.303
I CAN'T HAVE
YOU EATING THIS STUFF.

00:04.340 --> 00:06.308
EXCUSE ME, YOUR GRANDMOTHER'S
GOT ME EATING NOTHING

00:06.350 --> 00:07.658
BUT GRASS AND TWIGS.

00:07.690 --> 00:10.818
YES, BECAUSE YOU
JUST HAD HEART SURGERY.

00:10.870 --> 00:13.270
- UGH. PLEASE.
- SHE SEES ME BONDING WITH RUBY,

00:13.320 --> 00:14.457
THAT'S THREATENING TO HER.

00:14.490 --> 00:16.378
SHE THINKS I'M TAKING HER PLACE.

00:16.430 --> 00:18.079
IT'S A BIGGER ISSUE.

00:18.120 --> 00:20.384
A YEAR AGO YOU
ASKED ME TO FIGHT FOR YOU.

00:20.430 --> 00:22.807
I'M FIGHTING FOR YOU AND I'M
FIGHTING FOR OUR MARRIAGE.

00:22.850 --> 00:24.397
I WANT YOU BACK.

00:24.430 --> 00:27.467
HE KEEPS ASKING ME WHY I LIKE AARON, AND I'M SORRY.

00:27.510 --> 00:29.774
I'M NEVER GONNA LIKE MAX,
LIKE, IN THAT WAY.

00:31.890 --> 00:33.858
OKAY, BEN,
WE'LL START WITH YOU.

00:33.890 --> 00:36.370
GO FOR IT, WITH GUSTO.

00:36.410 --> 00:38.549
- SALVE PARENTES.
- OKAY, THAT WAS SO GOOD

00:38.590 --> 00:40.091
BUT LET'S TRY THAT
ONE MORE TIME LIKE--

00:40.140 --> 00:41.539
SALVE PARENTES!

00:41.590 --> 00:44.275
YOU, COULD EVEN, LIKE, ALMOST
SING IT IF YOU WANT, OKAY?

00:44.320 --> 00:46.766
- SALVE PARENTES!
- SO GOOD.

00:46.800 --> 00:49.553
THAT WAS SO GOOD, OKAY,
AMY, GIVE ME WHAT YOU GOT.

00:49.600 --> 00:52.114
TODAY, WE'RE GOING
TO TAKE YOU ON A TOUR

00:52.150 --> 00:54.732
AND TEACH YOU ABOUT THE FORUM,
THE COLISEUM,

00:54.770 --> 00:56.351
AND OUR FAMOUS AQUEDUCTS.

00:56.400 --> 00:59.221
OKAY, SWEETHEART WHEN YOU
SPEAK I WANT YOU TO LOOK UP

00:59.260 --> 01:01.319
AND SORT OF HAVE
MORE EYE CONTACT WITH ME--

01:01.370 --> 01:02.632
- HEY, MR. B?
- HOLD ON ONE SECOND,

01:02.680 --> 01:03.465
- CAN I TALK TO YOU?
- WE'RE PREPPING FOR OPEN
HOUSE...

01:03.510 --> 01:04.465
NO, NO, I KNOW,
THIS IS ABOUT THAT.

01:04.510 --> 01:05.818
NOW, JUST DON'T LOSE
YOUR TRAIN OF THOUGHT--

01:05.850 --> 01:06.817
- MRS. B?
- YES...

01:06.850 --> 01:08.499
THIS IS REALLY IMPORTANT.

01:08.550 --> 01:09.471
THIS IS ABOUT THE OPEN HOUSE AND
I REALLY NEED TO TALK TO YOU..

01:09.510 --> 01:10.169
- OKAY, SORRY--
- AND PROVIDED FRESH WATER--

01:10.200 --> 01:12.236
OKAY, SWEETHEART, WITH GUSTO,

01:12.270 --> 01:13.373
AND I'M GONNA
HAVE TO IRON THAT TOGA,

01:13.410 --> 01:14.616
OR STEAM IT OR SOMETHING.

01:14.660 --> 01:17.174
WHAT IS HAPPENING, BABE?
WHAT IS GOING ON?

01:17.210 --> 01:18.757
I CANNOT BE PARTNERS
WITH MAX ANYMORE.

01:18.800 --> 01:20.028
OKAY, HONEY,
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.650
- MRS. B.
- YOU GUYS HAVE
TO WORK ON BEING FRIENDS...

01:21.700 --> 01:24.351
- MRS. B. WOULD YOU--
- NO, I WANT TO BE FRIENDS WITH
HIM AND HE'S JUST LIKE...

01:24.390 --> 01:25.664
- MRS. B., WE'RE DOING IT AGAIN.
- HE'S PERSEVERATING LIKE,

01:25.700 --> 01:26.906
- I CAN'T, I CAN'T...
- MS. B. COME ON.

01:26.940 --> 01:27.907
I HAVE FAITH
THAT YOU CAN DO THIS...

01:27.940 --> 01:29.282
- AND I BELIEVE IN YOU.
- MRS. B.

01:29.330 --> 01:30.900
I KNOW YOU CAN DO THIS,
I KNOW YOU CAN.

01:30.950 --> 01:32.281
CAN YOU JUST SWITCH US
AROUND JUST FOR THIS?

01:32.330 --> 01:35.219
ALL RIGHT, YES,
OKAY, GOOD JOB.

01:35.260 --> 01:36.397
HI, DYLAN,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING NOW?

01:36.440 --> 01:37.668
- CLASS.
- ALL RIGHT.

01:37.710 --> 01:39.746
LET ME CARRY YOUR BOOKS FOR YOU.
IT'S A TRADITIONAL HIGH SCHOOL

01:39.780 --> 01:41.748
GESTURE THAT DEMONSTRATES
CHIVALRY AND STRENGTH.

01:41.790 --> 01:43.439
WHAT CLASS
ARE YOU GOING TO NEXT?

01:43.480 --> 01:45.232
IT'S A KITCHEN GADGET,
STARTS WITH A "P"...

01:45.270 --> 01:47.784
- HERE WE GO, FROTHY AND HOT.
- WHAT DID YOU CALL ME?

01:47.830 --> 01:49.548
- YEAH, IT'S GOOD.
- IT LOOKS VERY GOOD.

01:49.590 --> 01:51.649
- I'M GETTING BETTER.
- AAH! OH, MY GOD.

01:51.690 --> 01:52.679
- WHAT? WHAT?
- GUYS, GUYS!

01:52.730 --> 01:53.754
WHAT'S UP? YOU OKAY?

01:53.800 --> 01:54.698
OH MY GOD, NO,
I'M SO EXCITED.

01:54.730 --> 01:56.698
SAVANNAH HAS THE FLU.

01:56.730 --> 01:57.651
- SHE GOT THE FLU NOW.
- WHO'S THAT?

01:57.700 --> 01:58.837
- SAVANNAH...
- SHE'S...

01:58.870 --> 02:00.280
IN THE PLAY?
SAVANNAH IN THE PLAY?

02:00.320 --> 02:02.254
YEAH, SHE'S SUPPOSED
TO PLAY SANDY

02:02.290 --> 02:03.871
IN OUR PRODUCTION OF GREASE,
BUT NOW, IT'S GONNA BE ME,

02:03.910 --> 02:05.138
BECAUSE SHE HAS THE FLU.

02:05.190 --> 02:06.327
OH, MY GOSH,
SAVANNAH HAS THE FLU.

02:06.360 --> 02:07.349
- YEAH!
- THE UNDERSTUDY GOES ON.

02:07.400 --> 02:08.799
- YES! YES!
- OH, WOW!

02:08.850 --> 02:09.919
THAT'S GOOD.
THAT'S GOOD, RIGHT?

02:09.950 --> 02:10.939
DAD, YOU HAVE TO CALL MOM
AND, LIKE,

02:10.990 --> 02:12.434
- GET HER ON SPEAKER.
- OKAY, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

02:12.470 --> 02:13.778
WE COULD GET TICKETS
AND STUFF.

02:13.820 --> 02:15.742
- OH, THIS IS so...
- THERE'S A PERFORMANCE TONIGHT,

02:15.790 --> 02:16.779
AND THEN THERE'S
ONE TOMORROW NIGHT.

02:16.820 --> 02:18.742
YOUR GONNA DO THEM BOTH?
YOU GO ON TOMORROW, TOO?

02:18.790 --> 02:19.575
YEAH, I THINK SO.

02:19.620 --> 02:21.338
HEY, HEY, HEY, HERE'S RUBY,
HOLD ON.

02:21.380 --> 02:23.234
- I KNOW, IT'S AWESOME...
- TALK TO YOUR MOM, GO.

02:23.280 --> 02:25.441
OKAY, HEY, HEY MOM,
I'M PLAYING SANDY TONIGHT.

02:25.490 --> 02:26.752
YOU HAVE TO COME, PLEASE,
PLEASE, PLEASE.

02:26.800 --> 02:28.313
- OF COURSE I'LL BE THERE.- ALL RIGHT, AWESOME.

02:28.350 --> 02:29.419
WHO'S GONNA BUY TICKETS?

02:29.450 --> 02:31.270
SHOULD I BUY--I'LL BUY THEM,
RIGHT?

02:31.320 --> 02:33.106
RUBY, I LOVE YOU, I'LL SEE YOU TONIGHT, HONEY.

02:33.150 --> 02:35.425
HANK, CAN YOU PLEASE TAKE
ME OFF SPEAKER SO THAT WE
CAN COORDINATE?

02:35.460 --> 02:36.495
OKAY, I LOVE YOU.

02:36.530 --> 02:37.076
SO, IN
THE PAJAMA GAMEON BROADWAY,

02:37.120 --> 02:38.701
THE LEAD BROKE HER ANKLE

02:38.740 --> 02:40.879
AND THAT'S HOW SHIRLEY MACLAINE
BECAME A BIG STAR.

02:40.910 --> 02:42.639
DO YOU KNOW
WHO SHIRLEY MACLAINE IS?

02:42.670 --> 02:43.989
- YEAH, SHE--
- I'LL TELL YOU LATER.

02:44.020 --> 02:45.749
- DO YOU WANT TO RUN LINES?
- OKAY--YES, YEAH,

02:45.780 --> 02:46.815
I'M GONNA GO LEARN MY LINES,
ALL RIGHT.

02:46.850 --> 02:48.989
OKAY, OKAY,
OKAY, ALL RIGHT, BYE.

02:49.030 --> 02:50.429
ALL RIGHT,
SHE'S GONNA GET TICKETS.

02:50.480 --> 02:53.881
THAT'S SO EXCITING.
I CAN'T WAIT TO SEE HER.

02:53.930 --> 02:56.922
- OH, UH...
- OH.

02:56.960 --> 02:59.849
- HANG ON, LET ME CALL HER BACK.
- UH...

02:59.900 --> 03:01.936
WELL I'M GE'I'I'ING OLD

03:01.970 --> 03:03.449
BUT I'M NOT OLD YET

03:03.490 --> 03:04.764
HEY, GRANDSON,
KEEP THE CAR RUNNING.

03:04.800 --> 03:07.280
- I AM.
- GOT NO TIME FOR PLEASANTRIES,

03:07.320 --> 03:08.662
WE'RE ON A MISSION HERE.

03:08.700 --> 03:09.974
ZEEK?

03:10.010 --> 03:12.251
HEY, ZEEK, WAIT A MINUTE.

03:12.290 --> 03:13.325
- WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
- HUH?

03:13.360 --> 03:14.588
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

03:14.640 --> 03:16.949
YEAH, OH, BOY.

03:16.980 --> 03:18.777
YOU, YOU'RE TAKING HIM
FOR A HAMBURGER AGAIN?

03:18.810 --> 03:20.016
- YEAH, I KNOW ABOUT THAT.
- OH, GRANDMA...

03:20.060 --> 03:22.392
WAIT, DID YOU SNITCH
ABOUT THE BIG TOP BURGER?

03:22.440 --> 03:23.884
- YOU DID, DIDN'T YOU?
- HE DIDN'T HAVE TO SNITCH.

03:23.920 --> 03:26.480
I SMELLED IT ALL OVER YOU.
COME ON, ZEEK.

03:26.510 --> 03:27.738
WE'RE NOT GOING FOR BURGERS,
MILLIE, REALLY.

03:27.790 --> 03:28.927
WELL,
WHERE ARE YOU GOING THEN?

03:28.960 --> 03:29.881
HE'S GOT CLASSES YOU KNOW?

03:29.930 --> 03:31.022
OH, PLEASE CLASSES.

03:31.070 --> 03:32.401
- raspberry] GOSH!
- IT'S FINE.

03:32.450 --> 03:33.417
I MEAN, TELL
YOUR GRANDMOTHER HOW MUCH

03:33.450 --> 03:34.792
YOU ENJOY THESE OUTINGS,
WILL YOU?

03:34.830 --> 03:38.379
- TELL HER. COME ON.
- I MEAN, OBVIOUSLY...

03:38.420 --> 03:41.344
SEE HE'S SPEECHLESS, MILLIE,
HE CAN'T EVEN TALK ABOUT IT.

03:41.390 --> 03:42.789
LOOK, I'LL TELL YOU.
WE'RE NOT GONNA DO ANYTHING.

03:42.840 --> 03:44.046
WE'RE JUST GONNA
TAKE A LITTLE DRIVE, OKAY?

03:44.080 --> 03:45.832
BE RIGHT BACK.
I LOVE YOU.

03:45.880 --> 03:47.632
I LOVE YOU.
STEP ON THE GAS, LET'S GO.

03:47.670 --> 03:49.979
[whistles]
COME ON, LET'S GO.

03:50.020 --> 03:52.420
OKAY. GAS HIT.

03:52.470 --> 03:56.429
I WANNA DIE WITH A SMILE WHEN IT COMES MY TURN

03:56.470 --> 03:57.880
[door knock]
HEY, YOU.

03:57.920 --> 03:58.955
- HI.
- HI, HEY,

03:58.990 --> 04:00.332
KEEP TOMORROW OPEN BECAUSE

04:00.370 --> 04:02.053
YOU'RE HAVING LUNCH
WITH THE BOSS.

04:02.100 --> 04:04.307
TOMORROW I HAVE A LUNCH.

04:04.340 --> 04:06.069
ALL RIGHT, DINNER.

04:06.100 --> 04:08.728
OKAY, HEY, COME HERE.
I JUST--

04:08.760 --> 04:10.933
- I WANT TO TELL YOU SOMETHING.
- HMM? WHAT?

04:10.970 --> 04:12.278
- SHUT THE DOOR.
- UH-OH.

04:12.320 --> 04:15.721
NO, JUST I WANTED TO TELL YOU

04:15.770 --> 04:18.318
THAT I'M HAVING LUNCH
WITH JOEL TOMORROW.

04:18.360 --> 04:19.384
- OKAY.
- HE'S BEEN PUSHING

04:19.430 --> 04:21.079
AND I JUST FEEL LIKE

04:21.120 --> 04:25.329
I OWE HIM THIS MUCH.

04:25.360 --> 04:27.749
ALL RIGHT, WELL, YOU KNOW,
YOU DON'T ACTUALLY.

04:27.780 --> 04:29.054
YOU DON'T OWE HIM ANYTHING

04:29.090 --> 04:30.887
BUT, YOU KNOW,
YOU'RE BEING THE BIGGER PERSON

04:30.920 --> 04:34.299
AND I CAN RESPECT THAT.

04:34.340 --> 04:36.649
YEAH, I THINK IT'LL REALLY
HELP TO GIVE HIM CLOSURE,
AND THEN...

04:36.690 --> 04:38.066
MM-HMM.

04:38.100 --> 04:41.308
WE CAN BOTH FINALLY
SIGN THESE PAPERS.

04:41.350 --> 04:42.897
MOVE ON.

04:42.930 --> 04:44.727
HE'S BEEN DRAGGING HIS
FEET AND...

04:44.760 --> 04:49.311
YOU?

04:49.350 --> 04:50.999
CHRIS, YOU'RE RIGHT.

04:51.040 --> 04:54.043
IT'S TIME
TO STOP TREADING WATER.

04:54.080 --> 04:55.638
I WILL TELL HIM TOMORROW
AT LUNCH

04:55.670 --> 04:58.423
WE HAVE TO SIGN THE PAPERS.

05:02.780 --> 05:05.055
OKAY.

05:12.860 --> 05:15.658
WHEN WE WERE YOUNG
WE WERE SMALL

05:15.690 --> 05:18.966
BUT WE DIDN'T KNOW IT

05:19.000 --> 05:22.868
AH-AH-AH

05:22.900 --> 05:25.698
WHEN YOU WERE HURT
YOU WOULD SMILE

05:25.730 --> 05:29.143
SO YOU DIDN'T SHOW IT

05:29.190 --> 05:32.830
AH-AH-AH

05:32.880 --> 05:36.748
AND I

05:36.780 --> 05:39.772
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

05:44.440 --> 05:47.409
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

05:49.410 --> 05:54.791
CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'RE MINE

05:54.830 --> 05:56.695
GRANDPA, WE'RE GONNA
HAVE TO HAVE SOMETHING

05:56.730 --> 05:57.651
MORE SPECIFIC HERE BECAUSE

05:57.700 --> 05:58.928
THIS IS PRETTY BROAD.

05:58.970 --> 06:00.767
- GOOD, GOLLY.
- LIKE A NAME OF SOMETHING?

06:00.800 --> 06:02.176
IF I COULD DO THAT,
THEN I WOULDN'T NEED

06:02.220 --> 06:04.427
YOUR COMPUTER MAGIC,
GRANDSON.

06:04.460 --> 06:06.109
COME ON,
IT'S OVER 50 YEARS AGO.

06:06.150 --> 06:08.118
DREW, I'M JUST OUT
OF VIETNAM.

06:08.160 --> 06:09.184
I'D NEVER BEEN TO EUROPE.

06:09.230 --> 06:11.562
I'M LIKE 22 OR SOMETHING
LIKE THAT,

06:11.610 --> 06:13.987
AND I GET TO THE SOUTH OF FRANCE

06:14.020 --> 06:17.194
AND THERE'S
THIS LITTLE VILLAGE, RIGHT?

06:17.230 --> 06:21.610
AND I GO IN THERE AND THERE'S
THIS RUSTIC LITTLE INN,

06:21.650 --> 06:23.857
WITH THE IW AND ALL OF THAT.

06:23.900 --> 06:25.754
AND GUESS WHAT?
THEY SERVED THE BEST

06:25.790 --> 06:30.170
STEAK FRITES AND--AND RED WINE
I'VE EVER HAD IN MY ENTIRE LIFE.

06:30.210 --> 06:33.589
SO, ALL I WANT TO DO IS GET
BACK THERE WITH YOUR GRANDMOTHER

06:33.630 --> 06:36.667
AND SURPRISE HER
FOR OUR ANNIVERSARY.

06:36.700 --> 06:38.622
- RIGHT?
- YEAH.

06:38.670 --> 06:40.706
THAT'S ALL
THAT I'M INTERESTED IN.

06:40.740 --> 06:43.117
OKAY. DID YOU TALK
TO YOUR DOCTOR ABOUT IT?

06:43.160 --> 06:46.778
TRAVELLING OR FLYING?

06:46.820 --> 06:48.845
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?

06:48.890 --> 06:50.812
I WAS WONDERING
IF YOU'RE ALLOWED TO.

06:50.850 --> 06:52.647
- ALLOWED TO?
- YEAH.

06:52.680 --> 06:53.783
WELL, OF COURSE
I'M ALLOWED TO.

06:53.820 --> 06:54.809
WHAT DO YOU MEAN I'M
ALLOWED TO?

06:54.860 --> 06:55.781
I DIDN'T KNOW
BECAUSE OF THE...

06:55.820 --> 06:56.957
I'M AN ADULT FOR PETE'S SAKE.

06:57.000 --> 06:59.719
I CAN GO ON THE PLANE
AND I CAN FLY.

06:59.760 --> 07:01.614
I DON'T KNOW
IF YOU CAN BE HAVING RED WINE

07:01.660 --> 07:03.036
AND STEAK FRITES,
BY THE WAY.

07:03.070 --> 07:04.958
YOU SHOULDN'T BE WORRIED
ABOUT ANY OF THIS.

07:05.010 --> 07:06.796
WHAT YOU SHOULD BE DOING
IS GETTING ON THAT--

07:06.840 --> 07:09.172
WHAT DO YOU GOT THE WHOLE MAP
OF FRANCE UP FOR?

07:09.220 --> 07:11.074
BECAUSE THAT'S ALL
YOU'VE GIVEN ME. IT'S IN FRANCE.

07:11.120 --> 07:12.599
I SAID THE SOUTH OF FRANCE.

07:12.630 --> 07:14.040
CAN'T YOU--THERE'S A ZOOM
IN BUTTON.

07:14.080 --> 07:16.139
OH, MAN,
THIS IS GOING NOWHERE.

07:16.190 --> 07:19.910
WAIT--AH! IT JUST HIT ME,

07:19.950 --> 07:23.738
I THINK IT STARTED
WITH A "CHEZ" SOMETHING OR...

07:23.780 --> 07:27.193
- CHEZ?
- YEAH, LIKE A--OR LE.

07:27.230 --> 07:29.573
OR MAYBE IT WAS
A WOMAN'S NAME?

07:29.620 --> 07:31.929
BEGIN TO LOVE ME TODAY

07:34.970 --> 07:36.858
ACTUAL
CHARACTER NAMED DOODY?

07:36.900 --> 07:38.037
- DOODY.
- YEAH? THAT'S UNFORTUNATE.

07:38.070 --> 07:40.106
I FORGOT WHAT--
IT'S SHORT FOR SOMETHING.

07:40.140 --> 07:41.698
WHAT'S IT SHORT FOR?

07:41.730 --> 07:43.698
GOSH, I HAVEN'T SEEN THIS PLAY
IN SO LONG.

07:43.730 --> 07:46.665
HI, HELLO,

07:46.700 --> 07:48.941
I'M OBVIOUSLY NOT MRS. KING.

07:48.980 --> 07:50.800
AS SOME OF YOU ARE AWARE,

07:50.840 --> 07:54.185
THE FLU HAS BEEN GOING AROUND,
SO I AM THE ENGLISH TEACHER

07:54.230 --> 07:57.017
WHO KNOWS ABSOLUTELY NOTHING
ABOUT DRAMA

07:57.060 --> 08:00.814
BUT, UH...

08:00.850 --> 08:03.239
UM...

08:03.270 --> 08:07.024
BUT I DO KNOW THAT YOUR, UH--

08:07.070 --> 08:09.061
I KNOW THAT YOUR KIDS HAVE
WORKED INCREDIBLY HARD

08:09.100 --> 08:13.139
TO GIVE YOU AN AMAZING SHOW
TONIGHT, SO SIT BACK, RELAX,

08:13.180 --> 08:14.317
AND ENJOY.

08:14.350 --> 08:17.899
[applause]

08:17.940 --> 08:21.239
THAT'S THE ENGLISH TEACHER?
HI, HOT.

08:25.020 --> 08:26.567
I'M SO GLAD
YOU GUYS COULD MAKE IT.

08:26.600 --> 08:27.737
HEY, TOM. HEY, LIZ.

08:27.780 --> 08:28.872
- GOOD TO SEE YOU.
- GOOD TO SEE YOU.

08:28.920 --> 08:31.150
THANKS FOR COMING.
NOAH IS DOING SO WELL.

08:31.200 --> 08:32.849
HI, KATHY, HOW ARE YOU?

08:32.890 --> 08:34.881
- NICE TO SEE YOU.
- ZOEY'S LOVING IT HERE.

08:34.920 --> 08:36.603
SHE'S JUST LIKE A BRIGHT SPOT
IN OUR SCHOOL,

08:36.650 --> 08:37.856
SO THANK YOU SO MUCH.

08:37.890 --> 08:38.925
THANKS, I'M SO GLAD YOU GUYS
COULD COME.

08:38.960 --> 08:40.336
HAVE A SEAT AND WE'LL GET--

08:40.380 --> 08:41.779
THERE'S SOME MUNCHIES
OVER THERE, TOO.

08:41.830 --> 08:44.651
MR. AND MRS. JONES,
HOW ARE YOU?

08:44.690 --> 08:46.658
WE JUGGLED HALF A DOZEN
MEETINGS, BUT WE'RE HERE.

08:46.690 --> 08:48.965
I'M GLAD THAT YOU DID, BECAUSE
DYLAN IS DOING PHENOMENAL.

08:49.010 --> 08:50.272
SHE'S JUST SO SPECTACULAR.

08:50.320 --> 08:52.288
SHE'S A STAR STUDENT, SO...

08:52.320 --> 08:53.662
MAX, WE'VE BEEN
OVER THIS A MILLION TIMES.

08:53.700 --> 08:54.667
- CAN YOU JUST STOP?
- NO,

08:54.700 --> 08:57.146
I'M MORE HYGIENIC THAN HE IS.

08:57.190 --> 08:58.976
MAX, PLEASE. MAX,
PEOPLE ARE GONNA COME IN HERE...

08:59.020 --> 09:00.089
- I AM TALLER THAN HE IS...
- CAN YOU ERASE THAT?

09:00.120 --> 09:01.872
I AM MORE ATTRACTIVE
THAN HE IS...

09:01.920 --> 09:03.364
MAX, CAN YOU PLEASE ERASE
THAT?

09:03.400 --> 09:05.186
SO, I HAVE A PROOF UP HERE OF
WHY YOU SHOULD LIKE ME BUT IT...

09:05.230 --> 09:06.913
MAX, CAN YOU ERASE THAT
AND GET TO THE PRESENTATION?

09:06.960 --> 09:08.222
UNLESS YOU GIVE ME A LOGICAL
REASON WHY YOU LIKE HIM MORE...

09:08.270 --> 09:09.749
MAX,
THERE'S NO LOGICAL REASON.

09:09.790 --> 09:11.018
THAT'S NOT IT WORKS, OKAY?

09:11.060 --> 09:13.051
I'M JUST NOT INTERESTED
IN YOU IN THAT WAY.

09:13.100 --> 09:15.068
IS IT BECAUSE I HAVEN'T
DEMONSTRATED MY PHYSICAL

09:15.100 --> 09:16.681
AFFECT ION WHICH MEANS
I'M NOW IN THE FRIEND ZONE?

09:16.720 --> 09:18.278
NO, MAX, IT WASN'T THAT.

09:18.310 --> 09:20.722
DEMONSTRATING PHYSICAL
AFFECT ION IS A VERY DIFFICULT

09:20.760 --> 09:22.341
CONCEPT FOR ME BUT I CAN TRY.

09:22.380 --> 09:24.029
- MAX, PLEASE STOP, OKAY? MAX!
- OKAY, SO HERE WE HAVE...

09:24.080 --> 09:26.036
