LET'S GO, GRANDSON,
GOT NO TIME TO WASTE.

20:35.950 --> 20:37.747
GET IN THERE AND LET'S FIND
THIS PLACE.

20:37.780 --> 20:39.884
THAT'S IT.

20:39.920 --> 20:41.569
- OH, YEAH, THAT'S IT.
- THAT'S THE--OKAY.

20:41.610 --> 20:43.817
OKAY, TURN IT AROUND.
OH, LOOK.

20:43.860 --> 20:45.441
IS THAT IT?

20:45.480 --> 20:46.856
THAT'S IT. IT HASN'T CHANGED.

20:46.900 --> 20:48.344
YEAH, CH EZ MARIE.

20:48.380 --> 20:50.371
CH EZ MARIE?
SEE!

20:50.420 --> 20:51.967
I KNEW IT WAS A WOMAN'S NAME.

20:52.000 --> 20:55.458
THIS MIND IS LIKE
A STEEL TRAP, GRANDSON.

20:55.490 --> 20:57.867
- WELL, THAT'S IT.
- OKAY, HERE, THIS IS IT.

20:57.910 --> 20:59.286
LET'S DO IT.

20:59.320 --> 21:03.529
LET'S BOOK IT.

21:03.570 --> 21:06.562
- GRANDPA, I CAN'T BOOK IT.
- WHY CAN'T YOU BOOK IT?

21:06.610 --> 21:10.569
BECAUSE...

21:10.610 --> 21:14.671
GRANDMA KNOWS, GRANDPA.

21:14.720 --> 21:17.644
I'M SORRY, OKAY,

21:17.690 --> 21:20.443
BUT I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M
SUPPOSED TO DO WHEN SHE'S ASKING

21:20.480 --> 21:22.710
ME QUESTIONS ABOUT YOU BECAUSE
SHE'S WORRIED ABOUT YOUR HEALTH.

21:22.760 --> 21:24.443
SO, YOU TOLD HER?

21:24.490 --> 21:25.821
I DIDN'T TELL
HER EVERYTHING, NO.

21:25.870 --> 21:27.724
I ASKED HER IF IT WAS OKAY

21:27.760 --> 21:29.933
FOR YOU TO FLY BECAUSE SHE'S
ASKING ME WHAT WE'RE DOING,

21:29.970 --> 21:31.619
AND I'M TRYING
NOT TO TELL HER

21:31.660 --> 21:33.480
BECAUSE YOU DON'T WANT
ME TO TELL HER.

21:33.530 --> 21:35.805
BUT THEN I IN TURN
HAVE TO LIE TO HER.

21:35.840 --> 21:37.660
SO, WHAT AM I SUPPOSED
TO DO THERE, YOU KNOW?

21:37.710 --> 21:39.632
YOU'RE PUTTING ME
IN A REALLY WEIRD POSITION.

21:39.670 --> 21:41.467
AND SO, I TOLD HER
THAT YOU WERE GONNA--

21:41.500 --> 21:42.808
YOU WERE TRYING
TO FLY SOMEWHERE.

21:42.850 --> 21:48.368
THAT'S IT.

21:48.410 --> 21:51.743
GOD, YOU KNOW,

21:51.790 --> 21:54.782
THIS IS GONNA BE A SPECIAL TRIP,
DREW, YOU KNOW?

21:54.830 --> 21:56.684
YEAH, I KNOW.

21:56.720 --> 21:58.039
ME AND YOUR GRANDMOTHER,

21:58.070 --> 22:00.755
MAYBE FOR THE LAST--

22:00.800 --> 22:05.624
OH GOD.

22:05.660 --> 22:08.595
I CHOSE YOU
BECAUSE I TRUSTED YOU.

22:08.630 --> 22:10.143
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?
I TRUSTED YOU.

22:10.190 --> 22:12.738
YEAH.

22:12.770 --> 22:15.352
YOU LET ME DOWN.

22:15.400 --> 22:17.391
DO YOU UNDERSTAND?

22:19.820 --> 22:22.641
- JUST TAKE ME HOME.
- OKAY.

22:28.720 --> 22:30.062
[exhales]

22:30.100 --> 22:33.103
OH.

22:33.140 --> 22:34.584
- HI.
- HEY.

22:34.620 --> 22:37.032
- HOW'D IT GO?
- FINE.

22:37.070 --> 22:38.697
IT WAS FINE, CHRIS,
IT WAS FINE.

22:38.730 --> 22:41.858
IT WAS HARDER THAN I THOUGHT
SO I DIDN'T BRING UP THE PAPERS.

22:41.910 --> 22:43.172
DOESN'T MEAN I'M NOT.
THAT DOESN'T MEAN

22:43.220 --> 22:44.494
I'M HAVING
SECOND THOUGHTS, OKAY?

22:44.530 --> 22:45.383
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT, THOUGH.

22:45.430 --> 22:46.419
OKAY.

22:50.190 --> 22:52.841
BUT, JULES, WHERE DOES, UM,
WHERE DOES THAT LEAVE US?

22:52.880 --> 22:54.939
IN THE SAME PLACE.
NOTHING HAS CHANGED, CHRIS.

22:54.990 --> 22:56.469
EXACTLY, NOTHING HAS CHANGED.

22:56.510 --> 22:57.841
YEAH, WE'RE FINE.

23:01.650 --> 23:04.517
YOU KNOW, ACTUALLY WE'RE NOT.
WE'RE NOT FINE.

23:04.550 --> 23:05.778
I NEED SOMETHING.

23:05.830 --> 23:07.889
I NEED SOMETHING TO CHANGE,
JULES.

23:07.930 --> 23:08.965
I NEED SOMETHING
MORE THAN THIS.

23:09.000 --> 23:10.797
I WANT SOMETHING MORE
THAN THIS,

23:10.830 --> 23:11.933
AND IF THIS ISN'T GONNA
MOVE FORWARD I DON'T KNOW--

23:11.970 --> 23:13.528
IT IS MOVING FORWARD.
I JUST--

23:13.560 --> 23:14.629
I NEED MORE TIME TO FIGURE
THINGS OUT.

23:14.660 --> 23:16.696
SO, YOU GONNA TELL ME WHAT
MORE TIME LOOKS LIKE.

23:16.740 --> 23:18.002
I DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT LOOKS LIKE.

23:18.050 --> 23:19.620
IS IT A WEEK, IS IT A DAY,
IS IT A MONTH...

23:19.670 --> 23:21.763
I CAN'T CALENDAR IT FOR YOU.
GET OUT OF MY FACE, CHRIS.

23:21.810 --> 23:23.038
I DON'T WANT
TO TALK ABOUT IT RIGHT NOW.

23:23.090 --> 23:24.660
NO, YOU KNOW WHAT?

23:24.710 --> 23:25.847
ACTUALLY, WE DO NEED
TO TALK ABOUT THIS RIGHT NOW.

23:25.880 --> 23:27.609
I HAVE BEEN MORE
THAN PATIENT WITH YOU.

23:27.640 --> 23:29.437
I HAVE DONE EVERYTHING
I POSSIBLY CAN,

23:29.470 --> 23:31.028
AND I DON'T THINK THAT IT'S
A MATTER OF TIME, JULIA.

23:31.060 --> 23:33.949
I DON'T THINK THAT IT MATTERS
HOW MUCH TIME I GIVE YOU

23:33.990 --> 23:35.025
BECAUSE I THINK YOU'RE STILL
IN LOVE WITH YOUR HUSBAND.

23:35.060 --> 23:36.755
I HAVE KIDS
WITH THE MAN, YES.

23:36.790 --> 23:38.542
I HAVE FEELINGS FOR HIM.
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

23:38.580 --> 23:43.825
STOP PRESSURING ME.

23:43.870 --> 23:45.963
PRESSURING YOU?

23:50.840 --> 23:52.626
OKAY, JULIA, ALL RIGHT.

23:52.670 --> 23:53.659
PRESSURE'S OFF.

23:55.570 --> 23:57.947
CHRIS.

23:57.980 --> 23:58.969
CHRIS!

24:01.640 --> 24:03.084
- HEY, MAX.
- HI, BUDDY.

24:03.130 --> 24:05.155
WE WANT TO TALK TO YOU
ABOUT WHAT HAPPENED WITH DYLAN,

24:05.200 --> 24:08.920
BECAUSE I FEEL
LIKE WE OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.

24:08.960 --> 24:10.712
I DON'T FEEL LIKE WE REALLY
GAVE YOU THE FULL PICTURE

24:10.750 --> 24:13.025
ABOUT WHAT CAN HAPPEN
IN RELATIONSHIPS.

24:13.070 --> 24:14.890
REMEMBER WHEN WE TALKED
ABOUT THE NUMBERS SCALE

24:14.930 --> 24:16.750
AND HOW THINGS CAN CHANGE?

24:16.800 --> 24:18.176
WELL, SOMETIMES THEY DON'T.

24:18.210 --> 24:20.132
SOMETIMES THEY'RE JUST STUCK
BECAUSE THE TWO PEOPLE

24:20.180 --> 24:23.968
WANT DIFFERENT THINGS.

24:24.010 --> 24:25.898
THAT'S CON FUSING.

24:25.940 --> 24:27.589
- IT IS CONFUSING.
- VERY CONFUSING.

24:27.630 --> 24:29.040
HOW ARE YOU SUPPOSED TO TELL
WHEN THE SCALE IS FLUID

24:29.080 --> 24:31.219
AND WHEN IT ISN'T?

24:31.260 --> 24:33.080
THAT'S EXACTLY WHAT WE WANT
TO TALK TO YOU ABOUT.

24:33.120 --> 24:35.008
SOMETIMES IT'S JUST DIFFICULT,
YOU KNOW,

24:35.050 --> 24:36.938
AND YOU CAN'T.

24:36.990 --> 24:39.811
YOU JUST SORT OF GAUGE
IT ON HOW THE PERSON RESPONDS,

24:39.850 --> 24:41.670
YOU KNOW,
AND WHAT THEY'RE TELLING YOU.

24:41.720 --> 24:43.711
AND YOU ALSO
HAVE TO RESPECT THEIR WISHES.

24:43.750 --> 24:47.129
LIKE, WITH DYLAN, YOU KNOW...

24:47.170 --> 24:51.129
YOU MIGHT WANT TO BE CLOSER TO
HER THAN SHE WANTS TO BE TO YOU.

24:51.170 --> 24:53.889
IT'S KIND OF LIKE
WHEN YOU GET A HUG FROM SOMEONE.

24:53.940 --> 24:55.316
EVEN ME SOMETIMES,
I'LL TRY AND HUG YOU

24:55.350 --> 24:57.147
AND YOU DON'T WANT THAT.

24:57.180 --> 24:59.592
SO, I'LL RESPECT THAT BOUNDARY
AND I WON'T KEEP HUGGING YOU.

24:59.630 --> 25:00.904
AND DYLAN MAY HAVE FELT

25:00.940 --> 25:02.180
OVERWHELMED
BY WHAT YOU WERE DOING...

25:02.220 --> 25:03.596
[Kristina]
AND SHE JUST
INTERPRETED IT DIFFERENTLY

25:03.640 --> 25:06.017
THAN HOW YOU WERE GIVING IT.

25:06.050 --> 25:09.986
DYLAN SAID
I WAS HARASSING HER.

25:10.020 --> 25:13.569
OKAY, WELL
YOU WEREN'T HARASSING HER.

25:13.610 --> 25:14.918
DO YOU--OKAY, MAX--

25:14.960 --> 25:16.268
HARASSMENT IS DEFINED
AS AGGRESSIVE

25:16.300 --> 25:18.928
OR INTIMIDATING PRESSURE.

25:18.960 --> 25:20.689
I WAS ONLY TRYING
TO DO NICE THINGS.

25:20.720 --> 25:22.199
[Kristina]
YES, AND YOU WERE
DOING NICE THINGS.

25:22.240 --> 25:24.208
[Adam]
YOU WERE.
IT WAS JUST TOO MUCH FOR DYLAN.

25:24.240 --> 25:26.754
WE'RE JUST SUGGESTING THAT YOU
PAY A LITTLE MORE ATTENTION

25:26.800 --> 25:28.654
TO THE FEEDBACK
YOU'RE GETTING FROM OTHER PEOPLE

25:28.690 --> 25:31.830
SO THAT YOU CAN FIGURE OUT
WHAT THEIR BOUNDARIES ARE.

25:31.870 --> 25:33.758
DOES THAT MAKE SENSE?

25:37.910 --> 25:41.084
AM I THE REASON
DYLAN'S LEAVING THE SCHOOL?

25:47.130 --> 25:48.643
I WAS JUST BACKSTAGE
WITH RUBY.

25:48.680 --> 25:51.296
- HOW'S SHE DOING?
- SHE'S IN ABSOLUTE HEAVEN...

25:51.340 --> 25:54.059
- GOOD.
- SHE'S POLITE, SHE'S ENGAGED,
SHE'S GRACIOUS.

25:54.100 --> 25:55.067
IT'S LIKE SOMEBODY
TOOK OUR TEENAGE DAUGHTER

25:55.100 --> 25:56.988
AND REPLACED HER
WITH SANDY FROM GREASE.

25:57.030 --> 25:58.918
- YEAH, YEAH, HEY.
- HI.

25:58.970 --> 26:01.109
- HI.
- HEY. HI, MARK.

26:01.140 --> 26:04.007
I'M SANDY.
HI, I'M RUBY'S MOM.

26:04.040 --> 26:06.201
- OH.
- SHE PLAYS SANDY, I'M SANDY.

26:06.250 --> 26:08.002
YOU GUYS WANT TO
CATCH UP, OR--

26:08.040 --> 26:08.938
I DIDN'T KNOW
YOU WERE GONNA BE--

26:08.980 --> 26:11.005
NO, I KNOW. I'M ACTUALLY

26:11.050 --> 26:14.599
JUST HERE ON OFFICIAL SUBSTITUTE
DRAMA TEACHER BUSINESS.

26:14.640 --> 26:19.805
SAVANNAH IS FEELING BETTER
AND SHE HAS DECIDED LAST MINUTE

26:19.850 --> 26:21.818
THAT SHE WANTS
TO GO ON AS SANDY.

26:21.850 --> 26:24.159
- LAST MINUTE.
- THEY CAN'T DO THAT, RIGHT?

26:24.200 --> 26:25.098
- WAIT, THAT'S...
- THEY--THEY CAN DO THAT?

26:25.130 --> 26:27.678
THAT'S NOT FAIR TO RUBY.

26:27.720 --> 26:29.779
I KNOW, I KNOW.

26:29.820 --> 26:32.163
I JUST FOUND OUT
AND I ALREADY TOLD RUBY,

26:32.210 --> 26:33.893
AND SHE'S REALLY UPSET.

26:33.930 --> 26:35.204
SHE SAYS SHE DOESN'T WANT
TO GO ON TONIGHT

26:35.240 --> 26:36.309
IF SHE'S JUST GONNA BE PART
OF THE CHORUS.

26:36.350 --> 26:37.897
SO, I JUST WANTED TO...

26:37.940 --> 26:39.271
- I THINK I'M GONNA GO IN...
- TELL YOU GUYS.

26:39.320 --> 26:40.719
AND TALK TO HER.

26:40.770 --> 26:43.238
HANK, COME ON.

26:43.290 --> 26:45.758
YEAH, OKAY, UM--
YOU WANT TO COME?

26:45.810 --> 26:47.766
I DON'T THINK
I SHOULD BE PART OF THAT.

26:47.810 --> 26:48.947
IT WAS NICE TO MEET YOU.
HANK?

26:48.980 --> 26:52.848
IT WAS NICE
TO MEET YOU TOO.

26:52.880 --> 26:55.440
- HI.
- WELL.

26:55.470 --> 26:57.267
SUBBING AS THE DRAMA TEACHER.

26:57.300 --> 26:58.915
- YES.
- DID NOT EXPECT THAT.

26:58.960 --> 27:00.712
- NEITHER DID I.
- TWIST.

27:00.750 --> 27:02.957
THIS FLU.

27:03.000 --> 27:04.991
I JUST KEEP SCREWING UP
MY LIFE.

27:05.030 --> 27:06.167
OH, YEAH?

27:06.210 --> 27:07.711
HOW DO YOU KEEP DOING THAT?

27:07.760 --> 27:09.068
WELL, I JUST RUINED
A REALLY GOOD THING

27:09.110 --> 27:10.759
WITH A REALLY GOOD GUY.

27:10.800 --> 27:11.755
- THAT GUY, CHRIS?
- MM-HMM.

27:11.800 --> 27:13.791
- FROM THE BARBECUE?
- MM-HMM.

27:13.830 --> 27:16.105
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHAT'D YOU DO?

27:16.150 --> 27:20.837
I JUST--I COULDN'T
CUT THE CORD WITH JOEL.

27:20.880 --> 27:22.836
HE'S MAKING THIS SO HARD.

27:22.880 --> 27:24.393
IT'S--

27:24.430 --> 27:25.283
HOW?

27:28.370 --> 27:30.770
WELL, HE WANTS TO
GET BACK TOGETHER.

27:34.720 --> 27:36.028
THAT'S A GOOD THING.

27:36.060 --> 27:38.096
I KNOW, I KNOW,
I KNOW YOU WOULD THINK THAT.

27:38.130 --> 27:40.337
IT'S JUST
THAT I HAVE TAKEN SO LONG

27:40.380 --> 27:44.487
TO GET TO BE OKAY WITHOUT HIM.

27:44.520 --> 27:46.249
AND SO HE CHOOSES NOW.

27:46.280 --> 27:47.827
IT'S...

27:47.870 --> 27:48.894
YOU'RE JUST TALKING
ABOUT TIMING.

27:48.940 --> 27:50.316
SOMETIMES TIMING SUCKS.

27:50.350 --> 27:55.185
IT'S--NO,
IT'S NOT JUST TIMING.

27:55.220 --> 27:57.734
HE BAILED ON ME.

27:57.770 --> 28:00.227
YEAH, HE SCREWED UP.

28:00.260 --> 28:01.295
HAVEN'T YOU EVER SCREWED UP?

28:01.330 --> 28:03.742
NO, I SCREWED UP HUGE,
OBVIOUSLY.

28:03.780 --> 28:04.883
THAT'S WHAT GOT US HERE.

28:04.920 --> 28:06.012
I MEAN, I KNOW THAT,

28:06.060 --> 28:10.952
BUT I NEVER GAVE UP THE FIGHT.

28:10.990 --> 28:12.093
THIS IS THE FIRST TIME

28:14.960 --> 28:19.238
AND I REALLY NEEDED HIM.

28:19.280 --> 28:21.202
AND HE WAS WEAK.

28:21.250 --> 28:24.037
IT BURNS

28:24.080 --> 28:25.900
NOW YOU ARE GONE

28:25.940 --> 28:29.216
YOU KNOW WHAT MARRIAGE IS,
SWEETIE?

28:29.250 --> 28:31.878
YOU KNOW WHAT IT'S ABOUT?

28:31.910 --> 28:33.775
FORGIVENESS.

28:33.810 --> 28:35.869
IT BURNS

28:35.920 --> 28:40.129
NOW YOU ARE GONE,
I AM DONE

28:44.410 --> 28:47.925
I DON'T THINK I CAN.

28:47.960 --> 28:50.406
[Sarah]
DREW IS AT BERKELEY,
HE'S DOING WELL.

28:50.450 --> 28:53.305
- OH, YEAH.
- HE DOESN'T CALL ME ENOUGH.

28:53.350 --> 28:56.274
- UH...
- AND HOW'S AMBER?

28:56.320 --> 28:58.311
AMBER IS PREGNANT.

28:59.910 --> 29:01.070
WOW! WITH--

29:01.110 --> 29:03.522
IT'S--WELL,
IT'S A SITUATION

29:03.560 --> 29:06.074
WITH A BOYFRIEND WHO MIGHT
NOT BE IN THE PICTURE

29:06.120 --> 29:08.907
BUT SHE'S HANDLING
IT REALLY WELL AND...

29:08.950 --> 29:10.156
YEAH, SHE CAN DO THAT.

29:10.190 --> 29:12.181
IT'S JUST ABOUT SIX
WEEKS AWAY.

29:12.230 --> 29:13.913
- WOW.
- BIG CHANGES.

29:13.950 --> 29:15.918
THAT IS--
SO, YOU'RE GONNA BE A...

29:15.960 --> 29:19.168
- NO, NO, NO...
- A THING? NO?

29:19.200 --> 29:20.576
WE DON'T SAY THAT, NO.

29:20.620 --> 29:21.757
- THAT WORD?
- NO.

29:21.790 --> 29:24.338
MAYBE THERE'S, THERE'S GOT
TO BE SOME COOL, HIP NEW WORD.

29:24.380 --> 29:25.335
- I'VE BEEN TRYING TO FIND IT.
- YEAH?

29:25.380 --> 29:27.132
IT HAS ELUDED ME.

29:27.170 --> 29:28.967
I'M NOT SURE
IT'S GONNA CATCH ON.

29:29.000 --> 29:32.072
THERE'S BEEN A WORD
FOR IT FOR A WHILE NOW.

29:32.110 --> 29:36.388
- OH, IT'S TRAUMATIC BUT...
- THAT'S EXCITING, WOW.

29:36.420 --> 29:41.141
THAT IS JUST AHEAD OF MY WIFE.

29:41.190 --> 29:42.976
- NO, REALLY?
- YEAH.

29:43.020 --> 29:44.533
- YOU'RE GONNA BE A DAD?
- YEAH.

29:44.570 --> 29:45.980
OH, WOW.

29:46.020 --> 29:47.226
YEAH.

29:47.260 --> 29:49.364
OH, THAT'S GREAT.

29:49.400 --> 29:50.571
YEAH, IT'S EXCITING.

29:50.610 --> 29:52.225
YOU'RE GONNA BE SO GREAT.

29:52.270 --> 29:54.056
THANKS, UM, I HOPE SO.

29:54.100 --> 29:56.921
AH, THAT MAKES ME HAPPY.

29:56.960 --> 29:58.473
- YEAH.
- THAT'S GREAT.

29:58.520 --> 30:03.139
YEAH, UH--

30:03.180 --> 30:04.829
YEAH, IT'S SO SURREAL

30:04.870 --> 30:07.862
BUT I'M LOOKING
FORWARD TO IT, I GUESS.

30:07.900 --> 30:11.108
THIS IS GONNA SOUND WEIRD,
BUT I'M--

30:11.150 --> 30:14.972
I'M GLAD I KNEW YOU.

30:15.020 --> 30:18.979
I'M GLAD I KNEW YOU, TOO.

30:19.020 --> 30:20.567
I'M REALLY GLAD
THAT I KNEW YOU.

30:20.610 --> 30:22.464
IT BURNS

30:22.510 --> 30:24.319
NOW YOU ARE GONE

30:24.370 --> 30:26.258
I AM DONE

30:26.300 --> 30:28.507
- HEY.
- HEY, HOW IS SHE?

30:28.550 --> 30:30.268
OH, YOU KNOW, A LOT OF DRAMA,
A LOT OF CRYING,

30:30.310 --> 30:32.471
SANDY'S TAKING HER BACK NOW.

30:32.520 --> 30:34.545
OKAY, LET'S GO.

30:34.590 --> 30:35.579
YEAH,
IF YOU WANT TO HANG STILL.

30:35.620 --> 30:39.135
- NO, NO.
- AHEM.

30:39.180 --> 30:42.206
WELL, IT WAS REALLY NICE
TO SEE YOU, AND GOOD LUCK

30:42.250 --> 30:46.664
BEING A WHATEVER WORD
YOU COME UP WITH.

30:46.700 --> 30:49.146
AND I'M SORRY ABOUT RUBY.

30:49.190 --> 30:51.909
OH, YEAH, YEAH,
SHE'S OKAY.

30:51.950 --> 30:52.632
THAN KS.

30:55.060 --> 30:56.982
OKAY, BYE.

31:14.040 --> 31:16.144
[exhales]

31:28.300 --> 31:32.600
[gurgling]

31:32.640 --> 31:34.608
YOU'RE STILL SORE
ABOUT THE TRIP?

31:34.650 --> 31:36.709
YEAH, YOU'RE DAMN RIGHT
I'M SORE ABOUT THE TRIP.

31:36.750 --> 31:38.331
GOD! I MEAN,

31:38.370 --> 31:40.167
I CAN'T EVEN DRIVE
MY OWN DAMN CAR.

31:40.200 --> 31:42.373
EVERYBODY'S TREATING ME
LIKE AN INVALID.

31:42.410 --> 31:44.344
I CAN'T EVEN SPEND
MY OWN MONEY

31:44.380 --> 31:46.063
WHEN I WANT TO SPEND IT
FOR WHAT I WANT TO DO WITH IT.

31:46.110 --> 31:47.611
NO, YOU CAN'T.

31:47.660 --> 31:49.173
NOT WHEN YOU'RE PLANNING
ON SNEAKING AROUND,

31:49.210 --> 31:51.246
DOING THINGS
THAT ARE BAD FOR YOUR HEALTH.

31:51.280 --> 31:54.932
WHERE WERE YOU GONNA
FLY OFF TO ANYWAY?

31:54.980 --> 31:56.629
FRANCE.

31:56.670 --> 32:00.185
- FRANCE?
- YEP, GONNA GO TO FRANCE.

32:00.220 --> 32:03.155
YEAH? WHAT WERE YOU
GONNA DO IN FRANCE?

32:03.190 --> 32:07.980
OKAY, WELL...

32:08.020 --> 32:10.409
DO YOU REMEMBER WHEN I WROTE YOU
AFTER I GOT OUT OF THE SERVICE

32:10.440 --> 32:13.989
AND I WAS IN THIS
LITTLE VILLAGE, WES,

32:14.030 --> 32:16.066
AND THEY HAD
THIS WONDERFUL B&B THERE

32:16.100 --> 32:19.206
WITH THE BEST FOOD AND
WINE I'VE EVER HAD?

32:19.240 --> 32:20.275
- YEAH, I REMEMBER THAT.
- YOU REMEMBER THAT?

32:20.310 --> 32:22.130
- YEAH, UH-HUH.
- OKAY, WELL,

32:22.180 --> 32:24.512
I WAS, UH--

32:24.560 --> 32:27.176
I WAS GONNA SURPRISE
YOU ON OUR ANNIVERSARY,

32:27.220 --> 32:29.176
AND I WAS GONNA
TAKE YOU THERE.

32:29.220 --> 32:32.041
BACK TO THE B&B

32:32.080 --> 32:35.049
AND I FIGURED YOU COULD PAINT
ALL YOU WANTED TO.

32:35.090 --> 32:37.046
I MEAN, HELL, YOU PAINTED
ALL OVER ITALY

32:37.090 --> 32:38.739
