THAT IT'S NOT A SURPRISE.

33:13.850 --> 33:17.297
BECAUSE WE CAN LOOK FORWARD
TO IT TOGETHER.

33:17.340 --> 33:22.334
- REALLY?
- YEAH.

33:22.370 --> 33:24.065
YOU THINK IT'S CHANGED?

33:24.100 --> 33:26.716
NO, NO, NO, NO,
NO, IT HASN'T CHANGED.

33:26.760 --> 33:27.749
HERE, YOU LOOK IT UP.

33:27.790 --> 33:29.417
THE LINK'S CALLED WES,

33:29.450 --> 33:32.487
AND THE B&B
IS CALLED CHEZ MARIE.

33:37.320 --> 33:39.356
[gaSPSJ

33:44.470 --> 33:47.359
[gasps] OH!

33:51.200 --> 33:52.747
OH!

33:52.780 --> 33:56.238
OH!

33:56.270 --> 33:59.068
OH, ZEEK!

34:19.570 --> 34:20.730
WANT A BEER?

34:20.780 --> 34:25.570
OH, NO. NO, NO, NO,
NO, NO, I'M OKAY.

34:25.610 --> 34:29.432
- ARE YOU OKAY?
- YEAH.

34:29.480 --> 34:32.335
YOU HAVEN'T SAID A WORD
SINCE WE LEFT SCHOOL.

34:36.900 --> 34:38.856
YOU'RE HAPPY, RIGHT?

34:41.800 --> 34:44.177
I MEAN IN GENERAL,
YOU'RE GOOD?

34:44.220 --> 34:46.529
BECAUSE I--'CAUSE I GOT
A LOT OF BAGGAGE.

34:46.560 --> 34:49.427
I KNOW I GOT A--
GOT A LOT OF STUFF,

34:49.460 --> 34:52.145
BUT--AND I GOT
A DAUGHTER WHO'S--

34:52.190 --> 34:54.636
SOMETIMES SHE'S AN ANGEL,
SOMETIMES SHE'S NOT.

34:54.670 --> 34:57.912
I GOT AN EX-WIFE
WHO'S VERY VOLATILE,

34:57.950 --> 35:01.841
AND I'M WEIRD, AND...

35:01.890 --> 35:03.164
LOT OF STUFF.

35:03.200 --> 35:07.159
LOT OF STUFF, AND...

35:07.200 --> 35:09.236
DO YOU THINK THAT YOU...

35:09.270 --> 35:11.921
LIKE, YOUR LIFE
WOULD BE BETTER...

35:11.970 --> 35:15.929
OR JUST SIMPLER IF...

35:15.970 --> 35:20.418
IF YOU'D CHOSEN HIM?

35:20.460 --> 35:22.451
I KNOW YOU'RE NOT
GOING BACK TO HIM.

35:22.490 --> 35:23.491
I KNOW THAT.
NOT NOW.

35:23.530 --> 35:25.873
THAT'S NOT WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.

35:25.910 --> 35:28.185
I'M JUST WONDERING.

35:28.220 --> 35:32.395
I GUESS I'M ASKING

35:32.440 --> 35:35.705
IS THIS REALLY WHERE
YOU WANT TO BE?

35:38.230 --> 35:39.504
SORRY, I'M SORRY.

35:39.550 --> 35:41.165
OH MY GOD,
NO, YOU JUST...

35:41.200 --> 35:42.827
EVERYTHING I SAY IS WRONG.

35:42.860 --> 35:44.475
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT I'M
GOING THROUGH, YOU JUST DON'T!

35:44.520 --> 35:45.714
- RUBY! NO, I AM TRYING TO.
- NO!

35:45.760 --> 35:47.580
OH, MY GOD.

35:47.620 --> 35:51.386
SHE IS IMPOSSIBLE.

35:51.420 --> 35:52.762
I'M SORRY, I'M SORRY,
I'M SORRY.

35:52.800 --> 35:54.688
I JUST--I DIDN'T KNOW
WHERE TO GO.

35:54.730 --> 35:57.528
I'M SORRY.

35:57.560 --> 35:59.448
WE LOVE THE PLACE.
THIS IS GREAT.

35:59.500 --> 36:01.809
- SORT OF A COUNTRY MODERN.
- IT'S JUST MODERN, YEAH

36:01.840 --> 36:02.772
- SO JUST MODERN.
- IT'S BEAUTIFUL.

36:02.810 --> 36:04.493
- I LOVE THE TILE WORK HERE, TOO
- THANK YOU.

36:04.540 --> 36:05.916
- THANKS.
- GUATEMALAN?

36:05.950 --> 36:09.465
I'LL GET YOU MY DESIGNER'S
NUMBER IF YOU WANT.

36:09.510 --> 36:10.716
OKAY, LISTEN
WE'RE REALLY SORRY.

36:10.750 --> 36:13.924
SORRY ABOUT COMING
OVER UNANNOUNCED SO LATE.

36:13.960 --> 36:18.408
I JUST--WE WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
FOR NOT ADDRESSING

36:18.450 --> 36:19.929
YOUR DAUGHTER'S NEEDS SOONER

36:19.970 --> 36:23.417
AND REALLY TAKING THEM
TO HEART.

36:23.450 --> 36:24.678
WELL, THANK YOU FOR THAT.

36:24.730 --> 36:26.823
IT'S NICE TO HEAR.

36:26.870 --> 36:28.724
BUT WE'RE ACTUALLY

36:28.770 --> 36:31.625
MOST CONCERNED ABOUT
THE SITUATION WITH YOUR SON.

36:31.670 --> 36:32.978
WE'D LIKE TO KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA DO ABOUT THAT.

36:33.010 --> 36:35.877
WELL, ACTUALLY, HE WOULD LIKE
TO APOLOGIZE TO DYLAN.

36:35.910 --> 36:37.844
ONLY IF SHE WANTS TO MEET ME
OUT OF HER OWN FREE WILL.

36:37.880 --> 36:39.939
IF NOT, THEN I CAN JUST
APOLOGIZE TO THE TWO OF YOU.

36:45.370 --> 36:46.985
MAYBE...YOU SHOULD...GO.

36:47.030 --> 36:50.545
I'LL GO GET HER.

36:56.800 --> 36:59.928
WE'VE BEEN OUT OF TOWN
TRAVELING A LOT FOR WORK,

36:59.970 --> 37:04.725
SO THANK YOU FOR THOSE OCCASIONS
WHEN YOU HOSTED DYLAN, THANKS.

37:04.770 --> 37:05.794
- WOW...
- THANKS. WE LOVED HAVING HER.

37:05.840 --> 37:06.864
NO PROBLEM IT'S A PLEASURE.

37:06.910 --> 37:07.934
WE WATCHED MOVIES, WE COOKED,

37:07.980 --> 37:09.356
WE BAKED, WE HUNG OUT...

37:09.390 --> 37:10.948
- YOU BAKED?
- WE BAKED.

37:10.980 --> 37:11.844
- THAT'S FUNNY.
- YEAH, CHOCOLATE CHIP AND...

37:11.880 --> 37:13.495
I HOPE YOU, YOU KNOW,

37:13.540 --> 37:15.019
DIDN'T GO CRAZY WITH THE SUGAR.
WE REALLY TRY TO LIMIT...

37:15.060 --> 37:16.812
NO, NO, NO,
KEPT A GOOD EYE ON THAT.

37:16.850 --> 37:18.909
YEAH, SO.

37:18.960 --> 37:21.679
- HEY.
- HI.

37:21.720 --> 37:23.574
HELLO, DYLAN.

37:23.620 --> 37:27.021
I WANT YOU TO KNOW THAT I'M
DEEPLY REPENTANT OF MY ACTIONS.

37:27.070 --> 37:28.924
I UNDERSTAND NOW THAT WHEN YOU
SAY YOU DON'T RECIPROCATE

37:28.970 --> 37:31.689
MY FEELINGS IT MEANS
THAT I NEED TO GIVE YOU SPACE.

37:31.730 --> 37:34.346
ALSO, IF YOU DO DECIDE
TO COME BACK TO CHAMBERS ACADEMY

37:34.390 --> 37:37.484
I PROMISE TO NEVER COME
NEAR YOU AGAIN IN ANY CAPACITY.

37:44.600 --> 37:46.488
WE'RE HOPING THAT YOU GUYS
WILL RECONSIDER

37:46.540 --> 37:49.600
AND STAY AT CHAMBERS.

37:56.370 --> 37:58.850
WELL, WE'RE NOT EXACTLY
CRAZY ABOUT THE IDEA

37:58.890 --> 38:01.950
OF CHANGING SCHOOLS IN
THE MIDDLE OF THE SCHOOL YEAR.

38:02.000 --> 38:03.649
IT'S SO DISRU PTIVE.

38:03.690 --> 38:08.104
- MM-HMM.
- YEAH, SO WE'LL, UH...

38:08.140 --> 38:11.837
I GUESS WE'LL JUST RE-EVALUATE
AT THE END OF THE YEAR.

38:11.870 --> 38:14.759
- YEAH?
- YEAH.

38:20.530 --> 38:21.940
SEE YOU AT SCHOOL TOMORROW,
ASPERGER'S.

38:21.980 --> 38:23.561
WHAT? DYLAN!

38:23.610 --> 38:24.770
I'VE NEVER EVEN HEARD
HER SAY THAT BEFORE.

38:24.810 --> 38:26.607
- IT'S OKAY.
- IT'S FINE.

38:26.640 --> 38:29.086
ALTHOUGH SOME MAY TAKE OFFENSE
TO THAT, IN HER CASE

38:29.130 --> 38:30.984
IT IS A TERM OF ENDEARMENT,
AND SO I UNDERSTAND.

38:31.030 --> 38:32.782
I TAKE NO OFFENSE.

38:36.830 --> 38:39.469
[door closes]
OH, HEY.

38:39.520 --> 38:41.659
ALL RIGHT,
SHE FINALLY STOPPED.

38:41.690 --> 38:45.626
30 MINUTES OF SOME CRYING,
A LITTLE BIT OF BRIBERY,

38:45.660 --> 38:49.619
AND...OH, GOD.

38:49.670 --> 38:50.932
BY THE WAY SHE'S GOT,
LIKE, POSTERS ALL OVER HER ROOM.

38:50.980 --> 38:52.663
I DON'T KNOW
WHERE SHE GETS THEM FROM.

38:52.700 --> 38:55.737
SHE'S GOT, LIKE, THE HALF-NAKED
GUY FROM THAT WEREWOLF SHOW.

38:55.780 --> 38:57.395
WHAT IS THAT ABOUT?
I DIDN'T HAVE THAT.

38:57.430 --> 38:59.057
I HAD, LIKE, A POSTER OF--

38:59.090 --> 39:01.058
I HAD THE ROBOT
FROM THE LOST IN SPACETHING.

39:01.090 --> 39:03.570
I DON'T--I DON'T KNOW
IF THAT'S HEALTHY.

39:03.610 --> 39:06.852
